      "id": "2038831730287870207",
      "text": "RT @BritHugoboom: Grokipedia is far superior to Wikipedia and it’s not even close, especially when it comes to neutrality.\n\nTake Evie’s Wik…",
      "created_at": "Tue Mar 31 04:12:18 +0000 2026",
      "lang": "en",
      "media": [],
      "retweet": {
        "id": "2038765295058227265",
        "text": "Grokipedia is far superior to Wikipedia and it’s not even close, especially when it comes to neutrality.\n\nTake Evie’s Wikipedia page:  it’s been the target of a years-long hit job by a group of leftist activist editors who are blatantly breaking Wiki’s own rules, and they do this by defending each other’s edits while claiming consensus. When a factual edit is made, it’s immediately reversed because they’re watching the page. \n\nGrokipedia actually stays neutral and summarizes facts. It pulls straight from our own website and social media pages to describe what kind of content we publish (shocking!), instead of letting some opinionated leftist journalist slap their spin on everything. \n\nIt reviews all sources, weighs bias, and references articles from the larger, widely trusted publications, instead of using Media Matters or Vice as “neutral sources” (lol). \n\nThis is such important work from xAI because all these LLMs are out there scraping Wikipedia for their answers. If Wikipedia is full of false info or pushing a heavily biased take, then every AI chatbot ends up repeating the same garbage.\n\nThank you @elonmusk.",
        "created_at": "Mon Mar 30 23:48:19 +0000 2026",
